Frank Williams, who played Reverend Timothy Farthing in the BBC’s Dad's Army, has died aged 90. The sad news was confirmed in a statement shared on Facebook by those close to him. The statement read: “So sorry to say that our beloved friend, colleague and actor, Frank Williams, passed away this morning. "He was almost 91, and we are grateful for all the years of joy, laughter and happiness he brought to so many. Thank you Frank!" READ MORE: Ex-Spandau Ballet singer Ross William Wild charged with rape